// GAP #3 (2026-04-19 audit)
// CLAIM: `yield` used in a non-async function silently emits as no-op.
// EFFECT: programmer writes `yield;` expecting coroutine behavior;
//         compiler accepts and generates `void go(void) { return; }`
//         with no indication that yield had no effect. Silent
//         semantic change (not memory-unsafe but very confusing).
// FIX APPROACH: in check_stmt NODE_YIELD, check `!c->in_async` and
//               emit "yield/await only allowed inside async function"
//               error. ~5 lines.

void go() {
    yield;                  // should be compile error — not in async
}

u32 main() {
    go();
    return 0;
}
